{"key":"processedPost-8716191","value":{"id":8716191,"first":8711473,"last":8719384,"when":1217703035,"utime":"08/02/08 09:50 PM","content":"Rye straw, as all cereal straws, works fine.&nbsp; Use whatever is available.<br /><br />\"Hay has been used in substrate preparation with success. I honestly don't know enough about it to be able to explain why it is something that is cautioned against on this site. \"<br /><br />The problem with hay is the seeds, which tend to contaminate easily.&nbsp; In addition, straw is round and hollow inside, thus it makes for lots of little paths for the mycelium, as well as numerous water reservoirs for holding moisture. Hay tends to be grassy and flat, not round and hollow. Here's a microscope photo of a cross section of straw.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-006/108452877-SEM_of_Straw.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-006/108452877-thumb_SEM_of_Straw.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: Rye straw..?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}